So why then don't we get a realm ability that turns a tank's weapon against him?  How about a RA that causes a champion to debuff himself?  And while we are at it with the bolt reflection, let's make the reflected bolt immune to con buffs and unhealable as well.  <P>Are there ANY other realm abilities that turn something you have to actually spec for against the person who specced for it?  Geez, in return for this I want my confuse to work on my realm enemies...how is this any different from having the pet I spec for attack me and be immune to my ONLY defense?  I'll tell you how...it's different because it only uses MY (confuse) ability and doesn't turn an ability they had to spec to get against them! That would be like confuse giving them a chance of hitting themselves too, which still would be less lethal to the tank, who has more hps, better armor, yadda yadda yadda.  Really, confuse working on enemy players would be far less obnoxious, but remember, taking control from sorcs...which is exactly what you do when you turn the pet on him and make it immune to his only defenses...is par for the course.  Taking it away from tanks in an less invasive way would be well, quite simply too "naughty" to contemplate.  <P>Talking to Mythic makes me feel like Scott Evil talking to his dad.  Morons.<P>Tequitus
